The paper proposes a framework for improving the efficiency and accuracy of Collaborative Filtering (CF) using binary codes and real-valued vectors. This work involves machine learning, data mining, and information retrieval techniques, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Databases (cs.DB).
